-- There's always `of`
-- Then one generator for each operation
-- Make it an equivalence relation:
-- There's always a `map` relation
-- Then one relation per operation, describing the interaction with `of`
-- Then one relation per argument of each operation
-- And one relation per axiom
@[simp]
theorem quot_one : Quot.mk Setoid.r one = (1 : colimit_type F) :=
  rfl
#align quot_one quot_one
quot_mul:
@[simp]
theorem quot_mul (x y) : Quot.mk Setoid.r (mul x y) = (Quot.mk Setoid.r x * Quot.mk Setoid.r y : colimit_type F) :=
  rfl
#align quot_mul quot_mul
cocone_naturality_components:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⟶ » -/
@[simp]
theorem cocone_naturality_components (j j' : J) (f : «expr ⟶ » j j') (x : F.obj j) :
    (cocone_morphism F j') (F.map f x) = (cocone_morphism F j) x :=
  by
  rw [← cocone_naturality F f]
  rfl
#align cocone_naturality_components cocone_naturality_components
cocone_naturality:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⟶ » -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ≫ » -/
@[simp]
theorem cocone_naturality {j j' : J} (f : «expr ⟶ » j j') :
    «expr ≫ » (F.map f) (cocone_morphism F j') = cocone_morphism F j :=
  by
  ext
  apply quot.sound
  apply Relation.Map
#align cocone_naturality cocone_naturality
